Joshua Quincy Burns was sentenced to three years' probation for second-degree child abuse after his daughter Naomi suffered several injuries . 
  He claims he grabbed her face when she slipped from his lap in March 2014 . 
  He was trying to save her from hitting her head on a coffee table . 
  He and his wife Brenda Burns say he is innocent and that the incident was 'an accident', not child abuse . 
  Brenda Burns has fled to Colorado to avoid being watched by the Department of Human Services . 
  Joshua Burns may lose parental rights to his daughter in June . 
 